  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a developer, I want to show the user that they issued the command before the result so that the action-consequence sequence is clearer.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: When issuing a `status.sendMessage` from a `handler` function, sometimes the message appears in the chat history _before_ the command's preview is shown. To the user, it looks like they issued the command after the result. Adding a busy-wait in the `handler` function doesn't solve the problem.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nThe command's `preview` is shown first, then any messages from the `handler`.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nSometimes it shows in the desired order, sometimes it doesn't. Seemingly at random.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Create a command with both a `preview` and `handler` function\r\n- Call `status.sendMessage` from the `handler`\r\n- Observe the results of multiple command issuances\r\n- See that sometimes the message appears before the command's preview\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.8-4-g024cf6d6+\r\n* Operating System: Android",
